Functional Requirements for E-Commerce Application

1. User Registration & Login
•	Customers should be able to register, log in, and log out using email/phone, social login (Google, Facebook, Microsoft) and password
•	The system should support password reset and basic profile management.

2. Product Catalog Management and Detail Pages
•	Customers should be able to view detailed product information, including images, specifications, price, stock status, and customer reviews.
•	The system should display high-resolution images for every product.
•	Products should be organized into categories.

3. Advanced Product Search & Filtering
•	The System should allow users to filter results by category, price range, brand, rating, and availability.

4. Shopping Cart & Wishlist
•	Customers should be able to add products to the cart, update quantities or remove items.
•	The system should allow users to save items for later (Wishlist) without leaving the current page.

5. Secure Checkout Process
•	Customers should be able to check out by providing shipping address, selecting delivery options, and reviewing the order summary and should allow guest checkout options for faster purchases.

6. Payment Processing
•	The system should support multiple payment methods (credit/debit cards, wallets, UPI, etc.).
•	Order summary and confirmation before payment should be supported

7. Tracking Order & Notifications
•	The system should send notifications (email/SMS/in-app) for order confirmation, payment status, and delivery updates.
•	Customers can view order history and shipping updates with tracking links 

8. Customer Reviews & Ratings
•	The system shall allow customers to leave star ratings, write reviews, and upload photos of the products they received
•	Customer Ratings should be displayed to help other buyers to make decisions.

9. Stock Management
•	The system should automatically decrease stock levels upon a successful order and notify Administrator to add, update, or remove products.
•	The system should be able to manage orders, update order status, and track sales

10. Responsive Design 
•	The system shall provide a seamless, fully functional experience across desktop, tablet, and mobile browsers.

11. Security management
•	The system should keep customer information safe and protected.
•	All payments and data transfers should be secured, so information cannot be read by others
•	The system should detect suspicious activities and use secure payment systems to prevent fraud

